Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.46,0:01:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,an excelsis Deo. Glory to God in the highest. By that alignment, we're united as one. You're
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.17,0:01:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,God's gift to me. I'm responsible for the truth of everything I say, and I take responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.48,0:01:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,for it on your behalf. I pray to God to speak through me every lecture that we give. Today
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.07,0:01:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,will be a somewhat difficult lecture, difficult to prepare at least, to explain insanity to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.76,0:01:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,people where rational is difficult. We're going to be speaking about relativism today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.92,0:01:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pope, you know, said that two things tearing down Western society, one of them
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.70,0:02:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is relativism. And so we decided to address the issue in some detail today. And I'm going
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.20,0:02:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to do that today. We have some slides, some new ones, very interesting. And so we'll do
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.03,0:02:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the best we can to try and...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.08,0:02:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We're having a little bit of technical difficulties. Just bear with me a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.96,0:02:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.38,0:02:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We live in a technologic world.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.19,0:02:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,In the world that I grew up, good and evil were compartmentalized. I didn't know anybody
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.47,0:02:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that was evil. We didn't know anything about evil except...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.68,0:02:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,God was out there someplace, Nazis or something. Life was simple. Everything was clearly demarcated.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.37,0:03:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In today's computerized internet, WWW intercom download, whatchamacallit world, they're mixed
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.72,0:03:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,together. And we confuse reality with the image. So I'll start out with a declaration
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.30,0:03:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,for the day. Everything is what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.96,0:03:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What it is is what it means. And what you think about it and how you label it is irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.22,0:03:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's up to you. Everything is the reality of its own existence. And that's what it means
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.77,0:03:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is what it is. What this hand means is what it is. You can call it anything you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.28,0:03:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You can call it victim. You can call it perpetrator.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.90,0:04:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. All right. How many people are new today? Okay. We have a lot of new slides,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.71,0:04:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,so we're going to spend most of the lecture on the new slides. But we will just do a fast
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.01,0:04:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,review of some of the basics for those that are new. Also, these are videotaped, and therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.43,0:04:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,people out there who haven't been to prior lectures want to see it. So I'll just present
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.80,0:04:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,some of the background.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.31,0:04:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So the pheno-kinesiologic method itself was a fortuitous discovery. I mean, its application
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.80,0:04:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to consciousness research was a fortuitous discovery, and I felt it was so important
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.55,0:04:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that I had to stop everything and do research on it. And it was a very important piece of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.50,0:05:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,work. So my dedication was pretty much like Sir Alexander Fleming. When Fleming discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.98,0:05:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,what penicillin was, it was a very important piece of work. But I believe it's a very important
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.51,0:05:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,could do he couldn't rest until he had gotten it across to the world because he
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.43,0:05:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,saw the implication of it comes out of all the pharmacology the cure of all the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.94,0:05:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,diseases when you know I had a huge practice for many years I practiced for
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.49,0:05:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,50 years when I started out the diseases that were prevalent you don't even see
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.25,0:05:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,anymore I can hardly believe but all the people all the people in the hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.63,0:05:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,where I went none of those diseases even exist how can that be that's due to all
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.24,0:05:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the wonders of science and the progression of our civilization all
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.45,0:05:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,right so we'll start off with just a review we could do number one which we
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.06,0:05:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,always do to give us an orientation now this skill of consciousness has become
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.38,0:06:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,relatively well known you realize it's an absolute scale
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.56,0:06:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.44,0:06:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it defines the absolute not which is relative if it's 38 degrees out is 38
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.80,0:06:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,degrees out according to this thermometer and that's an absolute fact
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.12,0:06:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't change how you think about it or whether you see yourself as a victim
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.04,0:06:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of the temperature map of consciousness then it gives us a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.81,0:06:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,common out of a common point of reference and it works pretty much like
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.72,0:06:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,a common out of a common point of reference and it works pretty much like
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.08,0:06:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,an altimeter or barometer or a thermometer it just gives you the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.00,0:06:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,temperature gauge of an energy field this energy field then has a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.12,0:07:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,physiologic response the physiologic response is shown most easily by the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.87,0:07:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiologic response but it's also showing many other ways yeah there's
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.57,0:07:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,in brain function, neurophysiology,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.37,0:07:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and as Carol has shown,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.86,0:07:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I just got a recent paper,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.56,0:07:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the update on the pupillometry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.57,0:07:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The pupil of the eye reacts
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.92,0:07:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,depending on the truth or falsehood of stimulus,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.51,0:07:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,irrespective of the person's personal opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.99,0:07:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The critics of it say, you know, it doesn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.20,0:07:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Kinesiology does not work in a lot of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.32,0:07:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who calibrate below 200 doesn't work at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.86,0:07:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And above 200, there's also a limitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.48,0:07:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So about a third of people in the United States
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.45,0:07:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,are capable of doing ordinary kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.20,0:07:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The criticism is people can't understand
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.88,0:07:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,what it means to be objective.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.67,0:08:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Objective means they'll say,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.85,0:08:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,well, you said so-and-so calibrated so-and-so.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.61,0:08:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't say it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.11,0:08:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care what they calibrated it at.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.68,0:08:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't the slightest interest on a personal level.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.56,0:08:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when you're doing
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.80,0:08:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,diagnosis, you just want to know the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.92,0:08:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,for its own sake, for its own sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.83,0:08:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That seems to be beyond some people's comprehension.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.17,0:08:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That you're interested in truth
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.61,0:08:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,for its own sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.43,0:08:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So I say if you have a biased opinion,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.35,0:08:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,first ask what the truth is,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.29,0:08:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and then decide on an opinion about that,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.94,0:08:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of in reverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.43,0:08:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And the letters we get, we can't make it work
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.99,0:08:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,because they go the other way around.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.49,0:08:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,First they have an opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.19,0:08:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,First they have an opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.33,0:08:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it doesn't corroborate
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.40,0:08:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,their opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.67,0:08:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It requires actually some sophistication
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.12,0:08:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to be consistently accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.64,0:08:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're trying to discern is essence
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.47,0:08:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,from appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.59,0:08:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Essence from appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.64,0:08:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Essence from appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.82,0:08:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,In this world, it's very difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.41,0:09:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because in our current society,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.60,0:09:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the perception of everything
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.86,0:09:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is politicized.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.13,0:09:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The perception, the image
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.08,0:09:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,has become
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.17,0:09:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is politicized.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.59,0:09:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.80,0:09:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,there's another layer on top
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.12,0:09:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,besides your own personal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.76,0:09:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There's your own personal politicized thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.95,0:09:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So everything is regimented
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.26,0:09:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,left and right, etc., etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.58,0:09:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Incorrect and not correct
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.94,0:09:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.32,0:09:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the map of consciousness then
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.74,0:09:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,came about
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.77,0:09:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,as a consequence of doing thousands
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.84,0:09:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of calibrations
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.79,0:09:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and seeing that energies were stratified.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.60,0:09:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Stratified.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.35,0:09:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And those that are aligned
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.42,0:09:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,with truth
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.07,0:09:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.28,0:09:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.38,0:09:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate from 200 up
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.28,0:09:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and those that are aligned
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.64,0:09:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,with falsehood
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.57,0:09:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,are 200 and down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.28,0:09:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,In psychiatry,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.38,0:09:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,these are called the negative
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.62,0:09:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,destructive emotions,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.97,0:09:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the emergency emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.04,0:10:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And these are the welfare emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.26,0:10:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Welfare emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.92,0:10:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So the level 200 then
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.07,0:10:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is above 200 is truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.21,0:10:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,below 200 is falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.13,0:10:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we'll see today,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.67,0:10:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it really delineates
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.96,0:10:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,two completely different
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.37,0:10:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,populations.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.22,0:10:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They are really two different cultures,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.24,0:10:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,very different cultures.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.03,0:10:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And they even have different
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.22,0:10:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,brain physiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.34,0:10:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Even brain physiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.24,0:10:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so, all right, next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.91,0:10:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We're just going to go fast
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.10,0:10:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,through the beginning slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.14,0:10:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This just shows the level
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.73,0:10:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.49,0:10:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and the energy level.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.75,0:10:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see as you get over
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.32,0:10:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,200,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.24,0:10:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it begins to rise very rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.58,0:10:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it goes all the way
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.05,0:10:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,up to the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.94,0:10:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.62,0:10:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So the higher levels
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.74,0:10:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,have to do with power.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.44,0:10:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The lower levels have to do
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.03,0:10:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,with force.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.02,0:11:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Force goes from here to there
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.09,0:11:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and it does something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.22,0:11:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It falls within the Newtonian paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.67,0:11:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Power doesn't go from
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.50,0:11:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,anywhere to anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.63,0:11:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It stands still
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.12,0:11:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and influences everything around it
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.87,0:11:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of the field
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.27,0:11:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.16,0:11:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Like gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.25,0:11:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It just stands there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.83,0:11:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But then influences everything
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.40,0:11:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,within its domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.69,0:11:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The distribution in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.10,0:11:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of the world's population,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.22,0:11:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we've got spots up there
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.00,0:11:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that are blotting out the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.45,0:11:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Approximately,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.48,0:11:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the world's population,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.32,0:11:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,around 80%
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.87,0:11:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.87,0:11:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In America, that's about 50%.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.53,0:11:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And there are some areas
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.54,0:11:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.19,0:11:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,where there's a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.83,0:11:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.23,0:11:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And there are some areas
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.28,0:11:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,where there's nobody above 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.67,0:11:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,There are whole countries
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.77,0:12:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,where practically nobody
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.01,0:12:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.94,0:12:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The entire culture is below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.58,0:12:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so we'll move
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.15,0:12:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,on to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.05,0:12:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is how they're distributed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.15,0:12:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,For those who have never seen it
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.22,0:12:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,before, it's self-explanatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.32,0:12:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Why doesn't the world just
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.63,0:12:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,self-destruct?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.63,0:12:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, because those
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.89,0:12:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,who calibrate above 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.51,0:12:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,although they compose a small
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.37,0:12:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,percentage, their power is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.86,0:12:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,so much greater, as you saw
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.67,0:12:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,from the level of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.86,0:12:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Even a few individuals
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.67,0:12:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,who calibrate extremely high
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.12,0:12:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,will practically counterbalance
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.77,0:12:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,most of the rest of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.12,0:12:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Their consciousness is so powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.01,0:12:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's because the numbers
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.29,0:12:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,as they go up are logarithmic,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.53,0:12:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,exponential in a logarithmic
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.46,0:12:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to the base 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.01,0:12:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So in each population,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.63,0:12:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you only really need a few individuals.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.00,0:12:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,There have been times,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.10,0:12:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,there have been centuries,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.22,0:13:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,where nobody was on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.34,0:13:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to calibrate over 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.11,0:13:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Many times, there's only a few.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.87,0:13:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, I think there's only,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.26,0:13:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot to count them,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.42,0:13:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but there's probably a dozen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.57,0:13:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So, but these are so powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.45,0:13:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that it counterbalances.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.16,0:13:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, human life would
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.88,0:13:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,really actually come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.80,0:13:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll move to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.16,0:13:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just a different way
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.42,0:13:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,of depicting the same balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.47,0:13:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That these few here
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.25,0:13:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,counterbalance the rest of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.37,0:13:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.61,0:13:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.91,0:13:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Percent of elapsed time
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.90,0:13:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of life on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.42,0:13:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And we were calibrating the level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.59,0:13:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.57,0:13:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,over great periods of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.50,0:13:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see that it just began
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.76,0:13:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to go up very, very recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.32,0:13:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we'll go to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.02,0:14:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,This chart, which we have shown many times,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.45,0:14:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,is interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.62,0:14:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It shows the level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.89,0:14:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of life on this planet
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.53,0:14:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,over great eons of time
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.27,0:14:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see that over great eons of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.88,0:14:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.36,0:14:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,has risen progressively.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.14,0:14:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In this is interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.80,0:14:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,because you see the origin
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.57,0:14:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and evolution of the ego itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.51,0:14:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not necessary to condemn the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.58,0:14:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and call it wicked, call it evil,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.03,0:14:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,beat yourself with sack cloth and ashes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.86,0:14:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see, it exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.41,0:14:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,evolved as a consequence of the nature of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.41,0:14:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,life itself. In the beginning there was only
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.13,0:14:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,when organic matter was hit by
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.91,0:14:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy field of divinity, life
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.20,0:15:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,evolved. So life evolved from life, not from
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.15,0:15:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,non-life. Let's see if that's correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.83,0:15:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Life evolved only from life itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.26,0:15:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Did not arrive from inorganic
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.84,0:15:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,non-life, so much from the bottom-up
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.46,0:15:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,theory of evolution. Anybody still
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.84,0:15:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,think life evolved from non-life? They've been weeded
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.01,0:15:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,out, I see. Put to death,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.37,0:15:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,which was kindly. Put them out of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.13,0:15:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,their misery. Well, anyway, lots of best-selling books
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.22,0:15:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,hold that life evolved from non-life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.84,0:15:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that's a defect of abstract thinking, because
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.72,0:15:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody who has any education realizes that those are different
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.62,0:15:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,levels of abstraction. Life is a totally different level
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.55,0:15:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of abstraction from mechanicalness and non-life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.37,0:16:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the beginning, then, the evolution of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.19,0:16:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,life, the radiance of divinity, the light of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.30,0:16:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,God, it says in Genesis, the light of God, when the radiance
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.90,0:16:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Godhead,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.00,0:16:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,arose the God of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.30,0:16:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But the God of creation was a manifestation
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.92,0:16:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Godhead, which just is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.04,0:16:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's expression, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.21,0:16:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,as the creator. When this energy then hit organic matter, life evolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.77,0:16:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In its most primitive form, life is not self-sustaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.65,0:16:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Life has to get energy, so the whole problem of the ego was,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.25,0:16:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the earliest forms of life had no form of intrinsic source of energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.50,0:17:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,such as chlorophyll. It had to seek and search and sample, and that's how the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.47,0:17:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,human ego began. It had to discern that which is poisonous, that which is food,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.25,0:17:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is nutritionist. And so this is a capacity of the ego to this day in
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.66,0:17:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the human mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.90,0:17:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,searches out there symbolically or actually physically
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.38,0:17:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to ascertain the qualities of that which is out there
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.59,0:17:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,so that it can begin to decide that which is agreeable
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.35,0:17:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and that which is disagreeable.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.24,0:17:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.84,0:17:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.93,0:17:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we saw that the animal kingdom reflected that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.33,0:17:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a new kitty.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.31,0:17:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,To keep you up on my wildlife at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.90,0:17:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a new kitty who calibrates.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.98,0:17:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll calibrate kitty.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.98,0:17:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates over Bootsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.61,0:17:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He's over 210, 220, 225, 226.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.01,0:17:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Bootsy's at 225.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.77,0:18:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to meet lots of people in this world
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.70,0:18:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that don't calibrate over 225.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.46,0:18:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Cost me 50 bucks, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.39,0:18:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to get my money's worth out of that cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.35,0:18:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So the evolution of the consciousness level
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.44,0:18:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of the animal kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.57,0:18:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is very, very informative.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.85,0:18:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.92,0:18:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And we start out very low
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.94,0:18:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you see this incredible evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.40,0:18:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What's it called?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.20,0:18:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Blue planet?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.05,0:18:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Blue planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.19,0:18:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you seen Blue Planet?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.63,0:18:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.21,0:19:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an incredible special, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.45,0:19:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,like Channel 8 or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.48,0:19:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it's subterranean.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.57,0:19:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes to the bottom of the sea
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.83,0:19:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see all these creatures living down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.49,0:19:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And their ingenuity,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.69,0:19:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just absolutely incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.00,0:19:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.50,0:19:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,To not be able to see intelligent design
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.90,0:19:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,within their intelligence
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.35,0:19:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is to really be blind
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.72,0:19:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,because these are very clever creatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.77,0:19:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, they pretend that they're a little fish
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.11,0:19:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and they hang out there
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.07,0:19:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and then their lights go on
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.44,0:19:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they quickly become the same as that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.96,0:19:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,which is attacking them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.20,0:19:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there's this marvelous intelligence
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.75,0:19:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and marvelous ingenuity.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.92,0:19:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The absolute genius of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.81,0:19:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The genius of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.14,0:19:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we go all the way from vipers,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.70,0:19:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Komodo dragons,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.03,0:19:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,reptiles, snakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.22,0:19:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't get into the pen with a Komodo dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.24,0:20:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And we come up through the whole animal kingdom here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.91,0:20:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see at about level, consciousness level 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.50,0:20:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you shift from the predators to the herbivores.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.43,0:20:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,These are exclusively reptilian
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.93,0:20:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.60,0:20:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Live solely by killing others.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.30,0:20:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And then around 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.58,0:20:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you see you shift to the elk,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.71,0:20:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the zebra, the giraffe, deer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.97,0:20:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's our family cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.19,0:20:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Dogs, family dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.50,0:20:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And you move on up
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.82,0:20:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see then how amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.61,0:20:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we see
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.38,0:20:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the most amazing thing
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.75,0:20:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is the cat and the dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.99,0:20:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The cat's purr
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.23,0:20:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.36,0:20:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And the dog's wagging tail
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.15,0:20:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.50,0:20:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And the cat's purr calibrates at 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.52,0:20:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the emergence of love
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.89,0:20:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in the animal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.98,0:20:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Love.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.41,0:20:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course the kitties I got at home,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.78,0:20:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,all you have to do is say,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.32,0:20:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,how are you today?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.10,0:21:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And they start going purr, purr, purr, purr.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.15,0:21:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The capacity to recognize
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.51,0:21:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and reciprocate to love
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.44,0:21:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is a very, very unique thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.35,0:21:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've always just been amazed at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.20,0:21:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The dog's wagging tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.24,0:21:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All you have to do is say,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.14,0:21:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,how are you, Bow-wow?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.92,0:21:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.18,0:21:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Bow-wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.48,0:21:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Bow-wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.52,0:21:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Man's best friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.10,0:21:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.36,0:21:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.33,0:21:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.22,0:21:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's up there already.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.18,0:21:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Good God.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.49,0:21:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The great books of the western world
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.78,0:21:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,serve as a point of reference.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.36,0:21:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Roughly they calibrate around 450.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.60,0:21:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget what, 455 or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.43,0:21:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, they calibrate in the mid 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.10,0:21:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's gonna be important to today's lecture
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.60,0:21:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,because this is the point of reference.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.91,0:21:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the great books of the western world
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.13,0:22:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,really evolved out of an extension of ancient Greece,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.69,0:22:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the golden age of Greece.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.13,0:22:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So the basis of our civilization
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.08,0:22:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is really the golden age of Greece.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.82,0:22:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And frankly, nothing has improved since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.07,0:22:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate to tell you,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.92,0:22:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but nothing has really improved
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.42,0:22:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,since the golden age of Greece.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.33,0:22:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And an intellectual, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.68,0:22:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world of the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.01,0:22:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we had the,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.35,0:22:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I was gonna say the period of the enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.31,0:22:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We came out of the dark ages,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.94,0:22:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the dark ages,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.27,0:22:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,black superstition and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.20,0:22:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have this golden age,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.29,0:22:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you might say, primarily in Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.42,0:22:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The great thinkers of all time,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.81,0:22:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the great books of the western world collectively,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.74,0:22:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,as I say, calibrate around 450, 460, around in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.32,0:22:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And I hate to tell you,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.59,0:22:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,but these are all dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.77,0:22:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,white men.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.68,0:23:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the oppressors of the proletariat.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.77,0:23:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted you to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.83,0:23:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,who the oppressors of mankind are,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.09,0:23:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because we're gonna talk about relativism today.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.00,0:23:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Logic and reason are oppressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.16,0:23:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Totalitarian, capitalistic, white men control.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.90,0:23:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.66,0:23:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So we will refute them then.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.61,0:23:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have St. Thomas Aquinas,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.38,0:23:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, the great saints of all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.42,0:23:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Aristotle, Socrates, Socrates is over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.55,0:23:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates, someplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.70,0:23:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, no, they're not,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.05,0:23:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,he's not in the great books of the western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.67,0:23:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, these are the great minds of history,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.25,0:24:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,great minds of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.31,0:24:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And we notice that the only thing that's peculiar,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.46,0:24:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's gonna be very important in understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.57,0:24:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,today's lecture,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.94,0:24:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is that they all calibrate in the like high 400s,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.27,0:24:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,mid 400s, intellectual integrity,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.68,0:24:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the world of the intellect,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.25,0:24:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,on our scale of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.31,0:24:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The 400s are quite high indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.25,0:24:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll notice that in the middle of it suddenly,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.65,0:24:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,what's that guy's name?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.54,0:24:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly you got Marx at 130.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.98,0:24:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And there you got the one apple that ruined the barrel.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.77,0:24:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,All it takes is one apple.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.44,0:24:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,One rotten apple to ruin the barrel.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.09,0:24:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And here he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.18,0:24:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And then of course he sided up with Engels.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.42,0:24:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Engels was at 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.77,0:24:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now Marx never worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.19,0:24:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He lived off Engels' family,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.06,0:25:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Engels was left a business by his family.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.30,0:25:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And Marx hung out, didn't have to work
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.36,0:25:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,because he hung out with a rich guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.89,0:25:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So here he talks about, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.05,0:25:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the fate of the worker, and he never was one.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.74,0:25:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He never was a worker.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.00,0:25:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I did more work than Marx ever did.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.98,0:25:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.48,0:25:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I did 10 times as much as Marx ever did.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.18,0:25:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I did 10 times as much work as Marx ever did.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.75,0:25:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't know anything about being a worker,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.85,0:25:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,for Christ's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.16,0:25:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He should have worked at the automobile factories
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.24,0:25:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,where I worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.07,0:25:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.52,0:25:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see what he thinks of his theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.25,0:25:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see what he thinks of his theories then, wise guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.56,0:25:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, these are the great minds,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.61,0:26:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the great minds, Sophocles, Shakespeare,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.40,0:26:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Plutarch, Plotinus, all the great names.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.57,0:26:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud, Galen, Harvey, and this is the whole world of science,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.88,0:26:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole world of science,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.00,0:26:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hippocrates and all of science, the great philosophers.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.63,0:26:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the great names throughout history.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.82,0:26:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Francis Bacon, Dostoevsky, Euclid, the geometry.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.35,0:26:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Hardly to be sniffed at, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.44,0:26:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we're gonna sniff at them today.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.18,0:26:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,These oppressors, they're gonna get their due.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.18,0:26:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.69,0:26:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all familiar with them for these lectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.35,0:26:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, intrinsic to today's lecture,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.27,0:26:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,or not intrinsic, but interestingly, we see that below 200
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.88,0:27:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,is the level that the brain has a different physiology
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.83,0:27:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,from those above 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.56,0:27:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, they warrant mercy and forgiveness,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.91,0:27:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,as the Lord Jesus Christ said,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.36,0:27:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,forgive them for they know not what they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.61,0:27:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,These people do not know what they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.49,0:27:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.46,0:27:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a statement of fact, for instance.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.70,0:27:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They do not know or realize that which they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.33,0:27:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, forgive them, Lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.44,0:27:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,for they know not what they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.18,0:27:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.66,0:27:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That's another reason they need a savior,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.31,0:27:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're incapable of realizing spiritual truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.70,0:27:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore, they need someone who will speak for them
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.16,0:27:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,before the Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.24,0:27:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the animal instinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.46,0:27:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,200 down is the narcissistic ego behind the animal,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.84,0:28:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,which is only interested in gain and survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.14,0:28:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Gain and survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.59,0:28:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's territorial, it's hegemonous.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.25,0:28:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You like that word, or hegemonous?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.85,0:28:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Dictionary says either way.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.24,0:28:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Chickened out.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.29,0:28:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This is hegemony, dominant, dominant, dominant.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.84,0:28:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's vilified politically,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.60,0:28:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and there are current fashionable philosophers
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.00,0:28:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that will tell you America deserves 9-11,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.98,0:28:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because America deserves the 9-11.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.05,0:28:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,because of its hegemony, because of its success.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.99,0:28:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that it's successful, it deserves to be attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.17,0:29:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, there's an interesting concept.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.32,0:29:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution wouldn't have gotten too far with that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.00,0:29:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we've evolved because that which is successful survives,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.47,0:29:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and that which is not does not.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.81,0:29:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so this is left brain physiology,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.22,0:29:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're dealing with the alarm reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.68,0:29:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You're dealing with the animal world.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.11,0:29:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you look at the world today, you'll see
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.35,0:29:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the difference between the alpha male and a wolf pack.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.91,0:29:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is like a bunch of wolf packs.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.28,0:29:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got an alpha male killing off rivals to be president or king or head monarch.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.64,0:29:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see turf wars.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.61,0:29:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Every country is like in a turf war with that around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.09,0:29:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the world of the wolf pack.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.50,0:29:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The wolf pack, the alpha male.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.59,0:29:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The wolf pack, the alpha male, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.14,0:29:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The dictator.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.29,0:30:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The dictator who calibrates 90 or 100 to 190 operates completely off this.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.96,0:30:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.14,0:30:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't see any compassionate.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.84,0:30:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They do not purr.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.13,0:30:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They do not wag their tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.16,0:30:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are nice to people like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.74,0:30:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,they will become paranoid and suspicious and have you executed
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.42,0:30:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,because they know you're up to something.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.44,0:30:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Because in their culture, people aren't nice unless they're looking for something.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.44,0:30:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't understand being nice for nice sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.69,0:30:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why we have difficulty dialoguing with that part of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.69,0:30:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We think, if we're really nice, they'll be nice to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.07,0:30:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.16,0:30:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.41,0:30:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So below 200, the world is linear, pedestrian, causality, Newtonian.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.44,0:30:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.50,0:31:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the alarm reaction, and people live off stress hormones.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.50,0:31:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, from 200 up, what happens?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.50,0:31:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The kundalini energy arises, the spiritual energy arises,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.50,0:31:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,within the etheric body, and it goes up through the chakra system.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.29,0:31:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And it completely changes your etheric brain and how it operates.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.29,0:31:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The etheric brain now becomes dominant,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.46,0:31:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and it goes through, instead of the alarm reaction,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.46,0:31:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it goes into your memory as a positive, positive feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.46,0:31:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the right brain puts out endorphins,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.46,0:31:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,which are healing and support your thymic gland and stress reactions.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.46,0:31:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, it increases healing and recovery, balancing the acupuncture system.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.75,0:31:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And you get a positive kinesiologic response.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.75,0:31:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the presence of this energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.75,0:31:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the alarm reaction sets in, the acupuncture system,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.94,0:31:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy system, your energy field goes down.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.98,0:32:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,When you hold this in mind, your energy field goes up,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.03,0:32:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and the kinesiologic response is positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.03,0:32:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And we know now from Carol that the pupil response also is similar.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.34,0:32:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,From stress, the pupil dilates,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.34,0:32:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and in peace, peace and harmony and love, it constricts.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.93,0:32:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So people who are critical of the kinesiologic response
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.93,0:32:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,try to make it like you're just finding out what you want to find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.05,0:32:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the pupillary response is not under voluntary control.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.05,0:32:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So that sort of dispels the critics of kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.38,0:32:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when done with a slit lamp,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.50,0:32:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,even though you don't see what the stimulus,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.50,0:32:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you can cloak the stimulus,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.50,0:32:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course we've done that on stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.53,0:32:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We've taken a fake painting, turning it around,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.53,0:32:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and a good painting is turning it around,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.53,0:32:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can't see what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.53,0:32:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And when she looks at the back of a fake painting,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.53,0:32:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,her arm goes weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.53,0:33:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,When she looks at the back of a true painting,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.53,0:33:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the arm goes strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.53,0:33:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's the energy of it then.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.53,0:33:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy of it then radiates out in a quantum world.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.53,0:33:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the other thing that's odd about the kinesiologic response
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.51,0:33:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and this whole phenomena is the physics of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.51,0:33:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're picking up is the energy field of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.81,0:33:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is non-linear, non-local.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.81,0:33:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no beginning, it has no end.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.07,0:33:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's outside of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.29,0:33:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's outside of time-space and it's outside of causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.29,0:33:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can't cause it to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.29,0:33:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It is what it is as a consequence of it being its own nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.29,0:33:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's outside of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.75,0:33:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the kinesiologic response,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.65,0:33:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you can ask anything about anywhere in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.65,0:34:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's out of locality,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.16,0:34:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,it has nothing to do with locality.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.16,0:34:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's non-linear, it has no local.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.16,0:34:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no center to the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.16,0:34:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So that which is infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.15,0:34:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is beyond time-space location or causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.15,0:34:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So not only can you ask anything about anything where in time,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.19,0:34:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you can also ask about anything anywhere in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.19,0:34:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're asking for the energy of an essence
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.32,0:34:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,which is beyond time and space
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.32,0:34:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and it has to do with essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.32,0:34:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Essence is a different domain altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.32,0:34:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They're also discovering,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.53,0:34:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,also having to do with the critics of kinesiology,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.78,0:34:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that biologic phenomena cannot be accurately studied
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.96,0:34:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,via Newtonian physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.09,0:34:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,For people who are scientifically educated,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.73,0:35:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Newtonian physics is not applicable to biologic phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.36,0:35:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.36,0:35:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Because biologic phenomena are regulated by a life energy
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.36,0:35:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Life energy is non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.36,0:35:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot delineate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.36,0:35:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The most recent discovery then
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.48,0:35:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is that what they're forgetting to define is
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.48,0:35:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy of life itself
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.48,0:35:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is intrinsic, of course, to all biologic phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.48,0:35:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore the Newtonian paradigm of reality is too restricted.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.48,0:35:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course we now have the Heisenberg principle
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.55,0:35:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that at least gives us some crossover
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.55,0:35:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,from the linear to the non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.55,0:35:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And we know that intention already changes
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.55,0:35:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the output.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.65,0:35:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you know, in talking with other physicians,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.65,0:35:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, we commonly had the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.65,0:35:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that somebody who'd been treated by all the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.65,0:35:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Newtonian strict medicine techniques
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.67,0:35:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,were incurable.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.67,0:35:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And a person who was non-traditional,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.78,0:35:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, just got them better by loving them.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.86,0:36:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a couple of old patients that couldn't quit practice
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.86,0:36:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so they left the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.86,0:36:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,because frankly their positive transference
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.86,0:36:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,was keeping them going.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.86,0:36:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said to Susan, I said,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.86,0:36:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I've only got two left.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.86,0:36:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally one went
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.86,0:36:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and then finally the last one went.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.28,0:36:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The last one who went was the guy
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.28,0:36:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that used to get me to light his cigarette
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.28,0:36:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,so he had an oxygen tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.88,0:36:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Newtonian paradigm of reality
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.88,0:36:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that would be foolish indeed, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.21,0:36:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, are you sure it's safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.21,0:36:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, yeah, I do it all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.21,0:36:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.00,0:36:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He passed on, of other things.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.05,0:36:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Then a nurse later told me
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.05,0:36:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that one time she'd done that
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.05,0:36:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and it blew the oxygen tank
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.05,0:36:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,right through the floor of the trailer.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.05,0:36:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So I didn't do that anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.05,0:36:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But I didn't have to
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.05,0:36:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because the last little guy left.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.05,0:36:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So then I closed my practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.57,0:36:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, now we'll go to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.44,0:37:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Level of consciousness and social problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.44,0:37:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Relativism would like to say
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.44,0:37:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,all social problems are based on
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.44,0:37:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the perpetrator-victim model.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.86,0:37:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So relativism is basically Marxism
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.86,0:37:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but with the name Marx removed.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.86,0:37:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always perpetrator and victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.05,0:37:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So the people that are at the bottom of society
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.36,0:37:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,according to that politicalization
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.36,0:37:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,are always the victims of those
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.36,0:37:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that are at the top of society.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.36,0:37:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't be poor anymore without being,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.55,0:37:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you're poor because you're a victim of somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.73,0:37:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the first 35 or 40 years of my life
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.96,0:37:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,being a victim then
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.96,0:37:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,because the reason I didn't have
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.17,0:37:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,more money is because
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.17,0:37:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,those bad guys had it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.69,0:37:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They had billions.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.69,0:37:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm writing this paper out
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.11,0:37:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to make $40 a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.61,0:38:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was a victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.36,0:38:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No money at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.38,0:38:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, the one reason there was no money
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.80,0:38:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,was that the Depression wasn't really over yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.15,0:38:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.15,0:38:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is related to the rate of employment.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.15,0:38:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Not to external bad guy predators at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.96,0:38:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.96,0:38:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can look at people in society
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.05,0:38:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that they are a cork.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.05,0:38:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Society is the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.05,0:38:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And each cork floats to the height of its own buoyancy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.40,0:38:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You can take a certain person
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.65,0:38:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and put him anywhere
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.65,0:38:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and he will come out a success.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.65,0:38:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can take other people
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.65,0:38:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and put them in the most advantageous circumstances
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.65,0:38:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and they will blow it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.65,0:38:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll blow it with a flash of hostility,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.92,0:39:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a flash of inappropriate jealousy,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.92,0:39:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,paranoia,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.92,0:39:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,inappropriateness somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.92,0:39:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They had it made and they just blew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.92,0:39:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because that side shows up.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.01,0:39:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.01,0:39:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So all the phenomena we see socially
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.88,0:39:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,are really evidence of the level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.88,0:39:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.88,0:39:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, even criminality is related to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.88,0:39:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness, race,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.01,0:39:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,weight is related to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.01,0:39:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Poverty, unemployment.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.01,0:39:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,All related to level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.01,0:39:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So that we could say within a certain field,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.01,0:39:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,certain phenomena are common to that field.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.01,0:39:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Common to that field.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.01,0:39:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So these fields then
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.01,0:39:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,are accompanied by these phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.65,0:39:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.65,0:39:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.30,0:39:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm bringing this up today
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.30,0:39:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,because we're talking about postmodernism
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.69,0:39:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and relativism.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.07,0:40:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you have the Louvre
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.65,0:40:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,which calibrates at 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.09,0:40:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So this image pictorially, artistically would represent
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.09,0:40:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say the great books of the Western world
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.09,0:40:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,which is traditional, beauty, aesthetics, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.96,0:40:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Then comes postmodernism.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.09,0:40:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was here and I couldn't believe it until I saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.09,0:40:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I said nobody would build something that looked like that
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.09,0:40:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in the middle of the Louvre.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.09,0:40:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.09,0:40:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, they did.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.61,0:40:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave it to the French.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.61,0:40:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.61,0:40:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This was back in the 80s.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.65,0:40:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, back in the 80s.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.65,0:40:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, this is the impact of what we're going to be talking about today
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.65,0:40:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,in visual form.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.65,0:40:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In visual form.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.65,0:40:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This thing here certainly looks nice all by itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.65,0:40:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the middle of the Louvre,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.84,0:41:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it's an insult.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.84,0:41:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.84,0:41:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really insulting to the beauty of the Louvre.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.84,0:41:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Insulting to the beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.23,0:41:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And inappropriate.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.23,0:41:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And from a certain viewpoint, grotesque.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.23,0:41:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Certain point of...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.55,0:41:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really an ugliness.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.78,0:41:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the extreme disparity.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.90,0:41:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We could take an alternate view
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.90,0:41:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and say that it's stark, cold glass,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.90,0:41:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,lack of historic,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.03,0:41:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,traditional beauty, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.03,0:41:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Brings out the beauty of the Louvre.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.30,0:41:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we'd be really postmodern.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.94,0:41:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We could think it sounds very smart and modern.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.21,0:41:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't think anybody would notice the beauty
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.21,0:41:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and historic authenticity of the Louvre.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.21,0:41:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So we put this abortion right in the middle of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.34,0:41:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So that you could go,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.34,0:42:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.78,0:42:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We take a picture of the Madonna
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.78,0:42:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and we put a tattoo on her shoulder, on her cheek.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.78,0:42:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought of doing that myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.78,0:42:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Take the Mona Lisa and put a tattoo right here, an anchor.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.92,0:42:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So that the viewer will notice her beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.92,0:42:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, thank you, perverse artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.82,0:42:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't realize she was beautiful
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.82,0:42:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,if you put that anchor on her cheek.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.82,0:42:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.26,0:42:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Take this abominable slide off of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.94,0:42:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.57,0:42:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.57,0:42:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this our slide list that we're doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.57,0:42:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, fashionable philosophies.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.13,0:42:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to get into them today.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.13,0:42:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The academic left 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.13,0:43:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody sort of knows that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.13,0:43:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Anarchism is about 100.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.38,0:43:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Atheism is about 165.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.38,0:43:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And I discovered why some people that I thought
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.38,0:43:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,shouldn't be having such problems do kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.48,0:43:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,One's a well-known professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.48,0:43:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.48,0:43:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is this guy only calibrating?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.48,0:43:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He couldn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.48,0:43:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And he writes against it and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.48,0:43:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He's at 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.48,0:43:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.53,0:43:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is this guy at 190?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.53,0:43:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He's out there for holistic medicine
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.53,0:43:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and professor and all that crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.53,0:43:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I discovered,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.53,0:43:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't even think of asking it,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.53,0:43:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,he's an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.53,0:43:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.86,0:43:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't lecture on atheism.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.86,0:43:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He lectures on good stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.86,0:43:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But the reason he can't get kinesiology to work
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.86,0:43:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is because he's below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.86,0:43:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.86,0:43:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.86,0:43:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll tell you right off the bat,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.86,0:43:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't work for atheists.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.86,0:43:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who deny the truth of God
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.59,0:43:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,are denied the gift of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.01,0:43:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So, karmically it makes sense, does it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.01,0:44:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If you refute the very source and authority
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.01,0:44:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and dignity of truth itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.01,0:44:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,then you're not allowed to benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.01,0:44:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, they're like disenfranchised.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.90,0:44:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.90,0:44:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to get into Marcuse's critical theory today,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.90,0:44:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's going to be a good part of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.90,0:44:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Deconstructionism,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.96,0:44:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,dialectical materialism
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.96,0:44:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is the essence of Marx.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.96,0:44:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.21,0:44:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,what happened a few decades ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.82,0:44:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,1950s,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.82,0:44:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget when,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.82,0:44:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,around in the 60s, 70s,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.86,0:44:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.92,0:44:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,To try and preserve,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.34,0:44:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,what happened is the Frankfurt School evolved,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.86,0:44:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in which various philosophers
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.86,0:44:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,tried to preserve the essence of Marx,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.90,0:44:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,dialectical materialism,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.90,0:44:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,by removing the name Marx
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.90,0:45:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and calling itself instead
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.32,0:45:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,a school of social theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.32,0:45:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,school of social theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.48,0:45:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But what you're going to see,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.48,0:45:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the modern world,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.53,0:45:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is nothing but that,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.53,0:45:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,dialectical materialism in new clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.30,0:45:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,These are just phenomena that we see,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.57,0:45:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,fascism and feminist politics,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.57,0:45:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody says,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.55,0:45:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you should vote for me because I'm a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.55,0:45:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that got to do with being president?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.07,0:45:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Or I'm black,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.07,0:45:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,or I'm Jewish.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.07,0:45:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that got to do with being president?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.07,0:45:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Being president has to do with understanding international politics,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.07,0:45:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the works of the United States government,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.07,0:45:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.07,0:45:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So they still play the sexism and color cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.07,0:45:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they're just cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.38,0:45:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.57,0:45:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Free speech in the United States
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.57,0:45:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is now down to 180,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.57,0:45:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and at the time of,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.57,0:45:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,1955 or so,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.65,0:46:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it was 255.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.65,0:46:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll get into those a little bit later.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.78,0:46:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And hate is a very popular product,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.78,0:46:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates around 70.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.78,0:46:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So news commentators and publicity people
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.86,0:46:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,get out there on panels and spew hate
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.86,0:46:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,because there's a big market.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.86,0:46:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Being hateful is profitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.90,0:46:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.94,0:46:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick way to wealth, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.94,0:46:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Irresponsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.46,0:46:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We notice that a thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.46,0:46:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,when it becomes an ism,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.46,0:46:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,drops to 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.67,0:46:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's going to be interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.67,0:46:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,because when we go to,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.84,0:46:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.84,0:46:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the new earth-warming theories and all,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.53,0:46:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens is it becomes like a crusade.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.53,0:46:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,A crusade.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.53,0:46:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So science is really damaged by these crusades
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.53,0:46:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in which they give research grants
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.53,0:46:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to people who agree with the political position.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.73,0:46:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.73,0:47:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.88,0:47:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,question of authority,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.88,0:47:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,these are names that we'll get into later.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.65,0:47:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We won't waste any time on them right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.90,0:47:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.90,0:47:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the essence of what's going on in the world then
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.90,0:47:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,is actually the core of Marxism
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.90,0:47:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,with the name Marx removed.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.13,0:47:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's the same dialectic materialism
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.13,0:47:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that makes everybody into victim and perpetrator.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.28,0:47:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.28,0:47:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Nutty professors are at 160.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.28,0:47:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, nutty professors will tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.34,0:47:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth is false and the false is truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.34,0:47:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That America bombed 9-11
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.55,0:47:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and God knows what all.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.55,0:47:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're very relativistic
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.55,0:47:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,until it comes to their paycheck.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.55,0:47:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.55,0:47:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,$10,000 is not a relativistic,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.55,0:47:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,$8,000, $6,000 is $10,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.55,0:48:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, well, things are only,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.55,0:48:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,if truth is only what they appear to be,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.55,0:48:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,then your lecture is only worth $10,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.55,0:48:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll give you $10,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.55,0:48:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you should be satisfied with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.55,0:48:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they're not relativistic
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.55,0:48:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,when it comes to money.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.69,0:48:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Money.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.84,0:48:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way you get them out of being totally crazy
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.84,0:48:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is to speak money to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.84,0:48:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Narcissism, 140.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.09,0:48:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.09,0:48:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But free speech, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.26,0:48:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in 2007 is 180.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.26,0:48:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Free speech in 1955,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.84,0:48:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,was 255.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.92,0:48:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So the modern electronic media
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.30,0:48:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,then are the royal road to hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.69,0:48:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they not?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.69,0:48:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.69,0:48:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.78,0:48:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,When I grew up, the bad guys were here
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.78,0:48:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and the good guys were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.78,0:49:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't have any problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.38,0:49:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't worry whether America secretly pulled off,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.17,0:49:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,what was it, the beginning of World War II?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.32,0:49:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.67,0:49:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't wonder if, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.82,0:49:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,President Roosevelt had done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.57,0:49:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me see.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.57,0:49:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this is the beginning of relativism versus reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.57,0:49:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can get into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.57,0:49:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.32,0:49:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,When we're talking about a scale of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.32,0:49:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,we're really dealing from absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.32,0:49:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolute is an amount of centigrade thermometer.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.32,0:49:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Water boils at 100 and it freezes at zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.32,0:49:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's an absolute phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.32,0:49:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It does not depend on what you think about it
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.32,0:49:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,or what its appearance is.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.32,0:49:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In relativism, perception is reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.09,0:50:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Not essence, perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.53,0:50:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So what it's saying is,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.59,0:50:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the sheep's clothing is what's real.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.82,0:50:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And don't mind the wolf underneath.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.82,0:50:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The sheep's clothing is what's real.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.82,0:50:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.17,0:50:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.17,0:50:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So discerning essence from appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.94,0:50:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that that's one of the most difficult things.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.17,0:50:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't happen within the individual
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.17,0:50:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,until about consciousness level 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.17,0:50:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,At 600, you pick up the essence of a thing
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.17,0:50:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and you glimpse the appearance,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.26,0:50:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but you know that's not what it really is.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.26,0:50:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's the opening of the third eye
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.61,0:50:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Buddhic body, one of the etheric bodies,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.61,0:50:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,which is above the crown chakra.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.69,0:50:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So discerning essence from appearance, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.51,0:50:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is at 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.51,0:50:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's, of course, what we do with consciousness calibration.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.90,0:51:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The science of consciousness calibration itself
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.15,0:51:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 605.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.15,0:51:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's God's gift to those of us
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.48,0:51:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,who would like to be able to see truth from a falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.48,0:51:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but are unable to do so for one reason or another.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.48,0:51:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.48,0:51:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So it, to me, is a gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.57,0:51:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We now have a means in which we can see
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.78,0:51:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth which formerly was only apparent
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.05,0:51:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to enlightened beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.05,0:51:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,600 is very rare.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.36,0:51:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There's probably nobody on the planet at 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.36,0:51:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And those who get to 600 leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.36,0:51:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Half of them leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.36,0:51:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in such an infinite state,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.00,0:51:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't even want to think about the infinite state,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.00,0:51:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that you want to evaporate.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.26,0:51:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You just want to dissolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.26,0:51:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So there is no inclination to come back to the world
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.34,0:51:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,or to deal with the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.34,0:51:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And the world, you know, as you see it,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.34,0:51:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't even matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.34,0:51:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, as you see it, it doesn't even exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.34,0:52:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, it's very rare then.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.57,0:52:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we've been given an awareness,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.73,0:52:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,a means to an awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.73,0:52:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that previously was only possible
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.73,0:52:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,for a couple of people in any generation,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.76,0:52:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and historically very few in number.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.76,0:52:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So I considered it, you know, an amazing gift,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.17,0:52:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,an amazing gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.17,0:52:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like discovering penicillin,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.17,0:52:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I could see the enormous benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.17,0:52:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It could come to mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.17,0:52:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I had to write about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.17,0:52:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's why I'm still here.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.17,0:52:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I could have been gone a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.40,0:52:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I intuited a contractual obligation.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.40,0:52:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I intuited that there had been an agreement,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.94,0:52:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and that I had not fulfilled that agreement yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.11,0:52:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,To discover a thing and then to explain it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.11,0:52:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.11,0:52:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So the agreement was...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.11,0:53:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So because of that, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.50,0:53:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,To discern...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.50,0:53:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is absolutism.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.50,0:53:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I get a kick out of these rambling critiques of our work, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.50,0:53:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of my members says,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.50,0:53:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Be forewarned, he's an absolutist.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.05,0:53:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Be forewarned, he's an absolutist?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.44,0:53:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Good God.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.88,0:53:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Mean truth is true and false is false?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.88,0:53:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.32,0:53:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds pretty oppressive to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.32,0:53:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What about my opinion?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.98,0:53:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So the alternate to absolutism,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.51,0:53:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is narcissism.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.15,0:53:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Which says perception is reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.46,0:53:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll see that's a dictum flashing on the TV screen very frequently now.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.53,0:54:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Perception is reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.53,0:54:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget about essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.53,0:54:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's what it looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.53,0:54:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Look how we package it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.53,0:54:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,If we make it pretty and frilly,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.53,0:54:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and smell nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.03,0:54:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This guy buys this car.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.03,0:54:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He sees this beautiful thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.03,0:54:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So seductive, she lays on this car.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.73,0:54:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He can't wait to get to the...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.73,0:54:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,To buy one.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.36,0:54:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a new Fousey.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.09,0:54:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the Brog?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.09,0:54:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you got one of them in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.30,0:54:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Seduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.46,0:54:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So what they do is they program you with this image,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.46,0:54:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,with this product.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.90,0:54:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So that you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.90,0:54:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Pavlovian reflex.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.90,0:54:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So that what you've been programmed to comes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.90,0:55:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And you say, I want it. I want it. I want it. I want it. I want it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.90,0:55:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Big juicy cupcake or big beautiful blonde.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.30,0:55:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget whether it's real.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.30,0:55:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Because perception is reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.30,0:55:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What you bought was the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.15,0:55:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I invented a new breakfast cereal called Gimmies.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.15,0:55:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Gimmies. Gimmies. Yum, yum, yum.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.34,0:55:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it's even got a clever advertising thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.53,0:55:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a little hand that comes out.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.53,0:55:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you put...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.53,0:55:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,When the clerk puts it in the grocery store,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.53,0:55:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,they move this, this little hand comes out.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.53,0:55:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It says, grab...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.53,0:55:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Or grab me. Grab me. Grab me.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.92,0:55:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Gimmie. Grab me. Gimmie. Grab me.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.69,0:55:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We could sell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.69,0:55:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you guarantee we could sell them?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.69,0:55:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, we could sell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.01,0:55:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Gimmies. Gimmie.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.65,0:55:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what's in the box is irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.90,0:56:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And it can't have an old flake or something in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.17,0:56:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they've already bought the Gimmie. Grab me.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.17,0:56:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And they've already got the yum, yum, yum, happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.71,0:56:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They just bought it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.71,0:56:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't care what's in the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.71,0:56:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The mother doesn't know what's in the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.32,0:56:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,She opens it, hopes it's nutritious.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.34,0:56:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What's important is whether it likes it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.98,0:56:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So absolutism is 650.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.98,0:56:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Relativism is 125 to 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.03,0:56:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's even lower than 125 sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.03,0:56:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Shockingly low.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.03,0:56:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So I want to do this one first.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.48,0:56:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,A wolf in sheep's clothing calibrates at 120.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.76,0:56:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the lowest energy of all the ones we're going to be talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.76,0:56:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The wolf in sheep's clothing calibrates at 120.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.46,0:57:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.84,0:57:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,120.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.84,0:57:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I was shocked when I rechecked it over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.92,0:57:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.09,0:57:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I can still believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.09,0:57:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The wolf in sheep's clothing calibrates at 120.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.09,0:57:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There is the warrant to the conscious, to the wary person,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.94,0:57:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to the enlightened person.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.53,0:57:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Because your destruction is masked as a sheep.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.13,0:57:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Your destruction is masked as a sheep.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.13,0:57:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And the media are very clever at providing sheep's clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.13,0:57:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it important to know?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.03,0:57:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in the long run, it probably isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.03,0:57:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.03,0:57:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if survival is important or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.32,0:57:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The world's interest in things being right is more important than survival, generally.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.53,0:57:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Being right.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.69,0:57:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.69,0:58:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So perception, then, is reality, is the basis of postmodernism.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.30,0:58:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see, Marx has the whole victim-perpetrator model.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.46,0:58:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's at 130.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.46,0:58:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,130.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.46,0:58:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And so these have some intellectual input to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.46,0:58:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So relativism, the philosophies of it, are generally higher than 130
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.46,0:58:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,because you've added some intellectual fluff into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.46,0:58:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.69,0:58:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The original, the originator, historically in ancient Greece,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.69,0:58:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is represented by Protagoras.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.69,0:58:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Protagoras at 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.13,0:58:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Protagoras' argument is this.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.86,0:58:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I live in my own reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.86,0:58:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What seems to me, you know, real is real to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.05,0:58:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You, on the other hand, live in your reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.53,0:58:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And what seems real to you is real to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.82,0:59:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, reality is merely perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.71,0:59:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,When Judas said, therefore, perception is only perception,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.71,0:59:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,not reality is perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.71,0:59:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What I think is reality, yes, it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.71,0:59:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,To some degree, that's solipsism.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.75,0:59:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Each person, you might say, lives in their own personal universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.75,0:59:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But most people of integrity realize that that doesn't mean
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.75,0:59:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that that's necessarily the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.75,0:59:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people are aware of the fact that that's the way they see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.75,0:59:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So the beginning of the downfall was represented,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.38,0:59:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,represented by Protagoras,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.21,0:59:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to whom his own statement was real.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.17,0:59:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It was then countered.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.17,0:59:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, your statement is not real either.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.50,1:00:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, your statement that what you think is real is real to you
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.50,1:00:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is also false.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.50,1:00:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So Protagoras couldn't prove his own theorem.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.61,1:00:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can't contradict a theorem, then it has no validity,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.61,1:00:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,because a true theorem is opposite and negates it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.69,1:00:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Protagoras' relativism really died around 400 and something B.C.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.94,1:00:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the most modern world hasn't gotten the word yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.90,1:00:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a dead argument in 450 B.C.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.42,1:00:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This argument was presented and shown to be fallacious even then.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.84,1:00:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can see what not reading the great books brings you to.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.48,1:00:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't even realize
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.48,1:00:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that all the things you're discussing were settled thousands of years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.48,1:00:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Thousands of years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.48,1:00:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.59,1:01:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Plato calibrated 485,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.01,1:01:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's in his discussions that this argument comes up with Protagoras.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.46,1:01:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see that Plato calibrates at 485.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.46,1:01:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So the modern world throws out Plato at 485
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.55,1:01:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and goes along with Protagoras at 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.55,1:01:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The fallen decline of Western civilization, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.55,1:01:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is in free fall right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.65,1:01:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It rejects Jesus, Buddha, and Krishna.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.69,1:01:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Relativism, postmodernism, hates all these creatures here.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.05,1:01:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They've calibrated at a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.05,1:01:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It would rather be an atheist at 165.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.05,1:01:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather be an atheist at 165.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.38,1:01:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why relativists can't do kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.82,1:01:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,To begin with.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.94,1:01:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They set out to disprove it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.21,1:01:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to prove the fallacy of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.94,1:02:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So they start out at 130.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.94,1:02:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It is what, you know, at 130,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.23,1:02:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in addition to which they're an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.23,1:02:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, of course it doesn't work for them.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.21,1:02:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want it to work for them.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.21,1:02:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want them to be able to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.30,1:02:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.30,1:02:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So that pretty much answers what that problem is.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.30,1:02:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the apostles at 990.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.38,1:02:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And here you balance that with skepticism at 130.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.38,1:02:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, should we believe Socrates at 570?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.01,1:02:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Or should we believe Noam Chomsky at 135 to 185?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.75,1:02:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Chomsky has replaced Socrates.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.73,1:02:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The great books of the Western world have been removed
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.73,1:03:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,by Harvard University.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.73,1:03:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Removed.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.67,1:03:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Removed.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.67,1:03:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,President of Columbia University currently is at 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.98,1:03:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,President William and Mary at 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.13,1:03:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The idea of you don't want to appear old fashioned.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.13,1:03:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to be, you know, be with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.28,1:03:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you throw out Socrates at 570.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.80,1:03:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And you adopt this politician, philosophical politician.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.53,1:03:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So are we going to have a break?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.82,1:03:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Four more minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.82,1:03:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, four minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.82,1:03:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We can do Chomsky in four minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.82,1:03:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we'll get to the philosophers later.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.03,1:03:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.57,1:03:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Science, you see, calibrates.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.57,1:03:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't seem like you've got to prove the value of science at 440 to 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.61,1:04:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Isaac Newton, Einstein, Freud, 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.61,1:04:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,From the viewpoint of relativism, science is oppressive at 160.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.26,1:04:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So the relativist is very anti-science.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.40,1:04:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Anti-science.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.40,1:04:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll notice that they're anti-science.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.40,1:04:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it has to do with logic and reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.40,1:04:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Logic and reason trumps perception.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.40,1:04:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, it has to be discarded.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.40,1:04:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So the anti-science bent then is sort of interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.61,1:04:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we live in a world in which science pervades everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.61,1:04:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And they will tell you that science is oppressive.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.82,1:04:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I really have to read you a few things to prepare you for the shocks.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.03,1:04:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll have a break in which they can recover.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.26,1:04:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The basic postmodern dictums of relativism.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.57,1:05:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You're an uneducated lot.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.05,1:05:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, my job is to educate you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.05,1:05:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how you got along without these amazing concepts.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.76,1:05:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we'll have a whole list of philosophers.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.34,1:05:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What we showed you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.34,1:05:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All the famous philosophers behind all this.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.34,1:05:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not going to believe this.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.92,1:05:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This is, I took it right out of the books.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.92,1:05:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've got the references right here.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.01,1:05:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The basic philosopher behind current modern postmodernism.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.30,1:05:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And the decline of the university.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.30,1:05:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Herbert Marcuse.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.30,1:05:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Marcuse.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.30,1:05:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Born in 1898.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.36,1:05:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Died in 1979.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.38,1:05:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Of unmentionable diseases and problems.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.38,1:05:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Marcuse is the main one.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.34,1:05:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The professors.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.75,1:05:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Who preach this.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.75,1:05:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Never read Marcuse.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.75,1:05:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They're like Marxists that never read Karl Marx.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.19,1:06:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Or Freudians that never read Freud.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.19,1:06:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They have never bothered to read it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.26,1:06:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I will then make you more educated than a college professor.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.05,1:06:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Postmodern dictums of relativism.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.69,1:06:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Fiction is truth and truth is fiction.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.69,1:06:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,How's that for a starter?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.57,1:06:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Herbert Marcuse.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.63,1:06:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Lying is legitimate.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.57,1:06:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Indoctrination is the purpose of education.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.51,1:06:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You thought you were sending your kids to college for education.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.00,1:06:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.00,1:06:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They're being indoctrinated.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.92,1:06:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard it with my own ears.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.92,1:06:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't have believed it but I heard it with my own ears.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.92,1:06:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In one flash this professor came out with an indoctrinating dictum.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.63,1:06:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.63,1:06:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Tolerance is really intolerance.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.13,1:06:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We should not be tolerant to conservatism.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.00,1:06:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It deserves to be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.00,1:07:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So, all words mean their opposite.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.44,1:07:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Tolerance really means intolerance.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.82,1:07:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Ethics and morality are repressive and totalitarian.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.11,1:07:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Conservation should be attacked.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.90,1:07:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,No, conservatism should be attacked and destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.61,1:07:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, at Duke University, things like that happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.61,1:07:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The choir went there.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.61,1:07:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if a conservative tries to speak in any public university,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.90,1:07:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,they're stoned, the crowds are there, pulled off the stage and attacked.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.90,1:07:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Marcuse recommends that.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.23,1:07:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That all conservatives be physically attacked and silenced.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.23,1:07:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All minorities are victims.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.65,1:07:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the grandest of all.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.11,1:07:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose of human life is sexualization, including that of children.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.11,1:08:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You should teach your kids all the various crafty perversions you can think of.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.30,1:08:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I've said it down backwards with children, rabbits, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.36,1:08:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Any weird perversion you can think of.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.40,1:08:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And these philosophers, they're the basis of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.50,1:08:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Personally led those kind of lives and very frequently died of the consequences of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.50,1:08:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose of life is sexualization, including that of children.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.61,1:08:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it he said? Drop something, tune in, drop out, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.06,1:08:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Sex and drugs and rock and roll, maybe.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.98,1:08:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemies of freedom are family.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.56,1:08:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the family is to be removed.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.18,1:08:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The state will come in and give your kids a sexual education on the various perversions
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.18,1:08:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,by the time they're in their 30s.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.18,1:08:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,By the time they're in third grade.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.90,1:08:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemies of freedom are family.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.90,1:08:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, because they stand for traditional values.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.90,1:08:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Religion, patriotism, work.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.97,1:09:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Work is for the fools.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.10,1:09:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Science, reason, logic.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.19,1:09:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Morality, capitalism, tradition, and God.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.55,1:09:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the enemies of freedom according to postmodernism specifically.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.22,1:09:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,A couple of very good books on the subject.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.32,1:09:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,For those parents that are in a matter of shock here.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.32,1:09:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not done yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.32,1:09:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to be in worse shock.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.86,1:09:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a book called All American Colleges.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.86,1:09:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This is 50 colleges that all calibrate at 440 or over.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.15,1:09:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give you the reference if you want.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.15,1:09:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll probably put it on our website.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.15,1:09:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's by the Intercollegiate Studies Institute out of Wilmington, Delaware.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.98,1:09:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,More about which I've just mentioned.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.98,1:09:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in a book called The Professors.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.98,1:09:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The Professors by Horowitz.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.98,1:10:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The one I like the best, although its title sounds somewhat insulting, is Intellectual Morons.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.77,1:10:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would you call anybody morons who said the truth is falsehood and falsehood is truth?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.77,1:10:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.67,1:10:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just being arbitrarily pejorative, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.67,1:10:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I have to give the audience a break.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.06,1:10:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Because what we're taking about is the fabric of current society.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.06,1:10:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The book I'm working on is called Spiritual Reality in Modern Man.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.06,1:10:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The Spiritual Reality in Modern Man.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.06,1:10:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Because modern man is up against things that traditional man never had to put up with.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.06,1:10:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He wasn't being programmed constantly, both liminally and subliminally, and consciously and unconsciously all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.06,1:10:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He wasn't being programmed.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.06,1:10:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it requires even greater than discernment than before.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.27,1:10:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of the slogans that flash in front of you constantly, don't forget they're repetitious.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.27,1:10:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Some commercials, I think I've probably seen them over a thousand times.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.47,1:11:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So just by sheer repetition, you become programmed.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.86,1:11:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So how can you ever reach spiritual reality in a world that is programming you with falsehood constantly, both consciously and unconsciously?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.86,1:11:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So we need to defend ourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.86,1:11:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And the way you defend yourself is you learn how to discern truth from essence, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.86,1:11:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And they have such prevailing qualities that after a while you automatically begin to pick up when you're being programmed and when you're being had.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.86,1:11:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's out of defense of everybody that I want us to stand up for truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.22,1:11:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Stand up for truth, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.43,1:11:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's really where we're at, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.50,1:11:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so we'll take a break. How long?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.50,1:11:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Fifteen minute break, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.97,1:12:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we're ready to restart?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.89,1:12:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, go, she says.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.69,1:12:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we gave you the fruit of these philosophers.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.81,1:12:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Now don't forget these professors who teach these concepts.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.14,1:12:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Never read the philosophic basis on which these came.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.47,1:12:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like being a rabid communist and you never read Karl Marx.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.18,1:12:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't even know if you agree with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.18,1:12:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know it's fashionable and it's a big parade and it's exciting.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.18,1:12:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get involved, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.10,1:13:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So I gave you a list because I want to be academically integrous myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.10,1:13:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The names of the philosophic, the basis of the philosophic theories.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.43,1:13:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll make these available in the book I'm writing right now, actually.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.43,1:13:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,One just died, Jean Baudrillard.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.46,1:13:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates at 175.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.15,1:13:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He said America deserved 9-11 because it's successful and imperialistic, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.15,1:13:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,John Caputo, these are names known in academia.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.47,1:13:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Noam Chomsky, of course they all calibrate at 130, 140, 150.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.69,1:13:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Gilles Daluz.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.69,1:13:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,190.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.69,1:13:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Jacques Derrida, 170.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.69,1:13:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Michael Foucault, very well known, 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.69,1:13:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Edmund Husserl, 195.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.93,1:13:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy Irrigary, 155.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.93,1:13:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Julia Kristeva, 150.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.11,1:14:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Fritz Kuhn, 195.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.59,1:14:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Jacques Lacan, 180.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.59,1:14:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Jean-Francois Lyotard, another well known name.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.59,1:14:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people have heard of that?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.97,1:14:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you make good professors, yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.69,1:14:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Mark Kuh is at 150.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.69,1:14:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, Mark's at 130.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.69,1:14:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Karl Popper at 185.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.69,1:14:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Jean-Paul Sartre, 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.69,1:14:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And now three well known names in academia.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.82,1:14:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter Singer, Gore Vidal, and Howard Zinn.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.38,1:14:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All below 200, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.06,1:14:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Those of you who are parents and struggle to get your kids through college,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.06,1:14:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm starting a new organization in which we are going to ask the universities for a refund.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.06,1:14:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The Ethical Refund Committee.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.93,1:14:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean this is what you were teaching my kid for my hard-earned money or the taxpayer's money, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.93,1:15:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Gee, thanks a lot.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.27,1:15:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I just learned something during the break that I didn't know what a hookup is.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.27,1:15:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought they were talking about hiccup, hiccup.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.06,1:15:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You go on this thing and you arrange a hiccup, a hookup.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.19,1:15:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It means a quick sex.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.48,1:15:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody goes on the internet, hookup, hookup with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.52,1:15:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't mean, I thought it meant go with them, you know, introduce them and become friends and all.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.52,1:15:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It means a quickie on the fly.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.53,1:15:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I just learned this.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.53,1:15:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.89,1:15:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what it means, you know that?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.57,1:15:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's shocking.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.57,1:15:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.89,1:15:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because I'm a repressive white male.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.89,1:15:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Conservative, probably.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.34,1:16:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the enemies of freedom are family, morality, ethics, religion, patriotism, work, science, reason, logic, ethics, morality, capitalism, tradition, and God.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.05,1:16:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I guess that takes care of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.85,1:16:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Back to being an old fogey, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.85,1:16:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.39,1:16:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So now, I'm going to try and give you the intellectual underpinnings of it because a lot of people get, as I say, videos of this.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.39,1:16:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of people study a lot of stuff off these lectures and they then look it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.39,1:16:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I want them to have the references of where to look it up so they don't think I'm just ranting.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.64,1:16:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in this side, I put that which is aligned with truth and integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.64,1:16:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.64,1:16:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Chivalry, Calvary, it's at 465.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.64,1:16:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I grew up in a world of chivalry.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.84,1:16:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody defended women.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.84,1:17:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Not to belittle them.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.84,1:17:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they honored them.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.13,1:17:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We honored women.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.13,1:17:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We stood up when a woman entered the room because we honored her.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.13,1:17:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't understand honor, that we were honoring her.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.13,1:17:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not belittling her.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.13,1:17:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We're honoring her.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.14,1:17:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I still find it difficult to watch a woman filling her own car at a gas tank at a filling station.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.14,1:17:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The world I grew up, nobody would allow a woman to get all greasy and dirty and crappy like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.14,1:17:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Then they came out and did it for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.14,1:17:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we did it not to belittle women, which is post-modernistic intellectual distortion,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.27,1:17:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,but because we loved them and honored them.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.27,1:17:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.27,1:17:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You get that difference, you see?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.72,1:17:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We weren't belittling them, saying you're too weak to do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.72,1:17:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, let me do that at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.94,1:17:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.94,1:17:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So, chivalry calibrates at 465.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.57,1:18:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Its downside is sexism at 180.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.86,1:18:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Its real downside is honor killing at 90.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.86,1:18:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,There are cultures in which if the woman gets raped, she goes to prison.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.93,1:18:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Pakistan, the prisons are full of women who were raped.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.93,1:18:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's her fault that she got raped.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.60,1:18:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there you're seeing the diametrically opposite of chivalry.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.60,1:18:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The chivalry, the man would be indignant about who raped the woman.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.60,1:18:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's the culture that stones her.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.60,1:18:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That stones her to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.82,1:18:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it doesn't honor killing, kills her family to preserve the family honor.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.88,1:18:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.88,1:18:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Orwell, in Orwell's 1984, predicted today's society extremely accurately.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.57,1:18:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And he predicted newspeak.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.57,1:18:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what is now called politically correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.57,1:19:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called newspeak.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.10,1:19:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.10,1:19:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.10,1:19:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And what did he calibrate?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.10,1:19:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,425.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.10,1:19:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And newspeak, you see, 180 is today's politicized social discord at 180.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.10,1:19:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,180.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.10,1:19:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, he predicted and now it's called newspeak.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.14,1:19:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it called politically correct?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.14,1:19:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called newspeak.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.14,1:19:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And he pointed out that newspeak was extremely oppressive.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.14,1:19:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the paradox of this is that the new freedom is more oppressive than the totalitarianism
Dialogue: 0,1:19:40.47,1:19:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that it alleges to displace.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.47,1:19:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You misspeak once, you just lost your job, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.02,1:19:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,All it takes is one.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.18,1:19:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here we have Orwell at four and a quarter.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.32,1:19:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Newspeak is now the language.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.32,1:20:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And on college campuses, newspeak is imperative.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.32,1:20:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, they have laws on the campus that you are not allowed to speak anything except
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.64,1:20:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,newspeak.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.22,1:20:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that you're only allowed on the campus to speak newspeak?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.09,1:20:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not allowed to talk about ethics, morality, all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.61,1:20:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Patriotism is not allowed on the college campus.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.14,1:20:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was in college, they had recruiters from various industries, companies, including
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.57,1:20:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the military.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.57,1:20:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the military was one option, which is, you know, a suitable option.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.64,1:20:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You can join the military, you can get an education, and if you come from a poor family,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.64,1:20:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,if it wasn't for the GI Bill, I never would have gotten through college, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.64,1:21:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So, but now, do you realize that the military is not allowed on the campus?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.15,1:21:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is the new freedom.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.15,1:21:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The new freedom is all kinds of languages cannot be spoken.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.53,1:21:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,No conservative clubs can meet on the campus.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.53,1:21:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The military recruiters are not allowed to recruit.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.53,1:21:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the new freedom.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.06,1:21:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And in newspeak, that's freedom.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.43,1:21:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,In newspeak, that's the new freedom.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.43,1:21:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if I couldn't have signed up for the Navy, I don't know how I would have gotten through medical school.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.02,1:21:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I signed up early when I was 17.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.98,1:21:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I got to the recruiting station, he says, you don't weigh enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.56,1:21:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, go home and eat bananas.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.17,1:21:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And he'll come back in two weeks.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.69,1:21:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I did.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.73,1:21:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I stuffed myself in bananas.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.73,1:21:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't stand a banana to this day.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.72,1:22:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I stuffed myself with bananas.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.84,1:22:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And I went back two weeks later, the same recruiting officer.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.93,1:22:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, get on the scale.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.93,1:22:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So, he put his thumb like this, and he said, you just make it 100 pounds.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.93,1:22:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He fudged about 4,500 pounds, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.78,1:22:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But his thumb was congenitally.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.78,1:22:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He did it so expertly.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.78,1:22:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, you just make 100 pounds.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.78,1:22:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.27,1:22:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,There's 1980.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.85,1:22:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, here we have Sigmund Freud, calibrated 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.46,1:22:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, I will say that I might have some prejudice because I had a Freudian signal analysis.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.46,1:22:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And my analyst was Abraham Karner, whose analyst was Sigmund Freud.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.50,1:22:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, he's my great-grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.50,1:22:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I might as well tell you that.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.50,1:23:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I might have a bias.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.50,1:23:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I'm not biased about the calibration.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.56,1:23:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The calibration is at 499, the same as Einstein.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.97,1:23:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The modern explanation of intra-psychic conflict is that it's caused that you're the victim,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.97,1:23:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and somebody is to blame that you're screwed up.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.97,1:23:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's somebody's fault.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.97,1:23:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's somebody's fault that you're.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.97,1:23:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I want to ask a question about this list of.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.14,1:23:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What I would call incorrectly crazy professors.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.73,1:23:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Taking them all off weird sex drugs and putting them on a mild anti-psychotic would have helped all of them resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.26,1:23:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If you read their personal lives, you'll see what I'm saying.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.69,1:23:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, their personal lives were so dissolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.69,1:24:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And they died of various venereal diseases and various things.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.72,1:24:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And sort of borderline schizophrenia.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.72,1:24:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The difference you see in schizophrenia.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.72,1:24:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't differentiate levels of abstraction.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.72,1:24:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't differentiate levels of abstraction.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.72,1:24:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, they cannot differentiate a label from the thing itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.72,1:24:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,To them, the label is the thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.94,1:24:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why they have such difficulty in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.94,1:24:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They cannot isolate levels of abstraction.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.94,1:24:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, Descartes.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.14,1:24:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, who was it?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.14,1:24:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Not Descartes.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.14,1:24:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The levels of abstraction are part of the teachings of the great books of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.14,1:24:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The Western world.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.14,1:24:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't mix levels of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.14,1:24:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, what's true at this level is not true at this level.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.14,1:24:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What's true in this situation is not true in that situation.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.14,1:24:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Because truth depends not only on content but also context.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.17,1:25:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what is legitimate or okay in one situation is not in another.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.30,1:25:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And these philosophers mixed up labels with reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.34,1:25:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remember the disaster that happened to psychiatrists.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.56,1:25:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a guy who wrote a book, Thomas Szasz, postmodern kind of thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.14,1:25:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And the whole concept of labeling.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.14,1:25:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no mentally ill.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.36,1:25:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are just labels.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.36,1:25:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.52,1:25:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's God telling him to kill people.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.72,1:25:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you can cure that usually with some kind of a medication.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.72,1:25:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the thing about mental illness is you can turn it on with a medication and turn it off with a medication.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.72,1:25:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing you change is the medication.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.85,1:25:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, it's not, you know, just a, they're not victims of society.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.42,1:25:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Free speech in 1955 calibrated at 255.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.46,1:26:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Free speech in today's world calibrates at 180.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.64,1:26:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I agree with Socrates that the downfall of democracy and Western civilization will be via free speech.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.06,1:26:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.06,1:26:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If you give everybody a chance to vote for what is and half the people calibrate below 200, what are you going to get out of it?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.57,1:26:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you going to get out of it?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.80,1:26:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If people cannot tell truth from falsehood, then where will it lead?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.43,1:26:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do the calibration level of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.43,1:26:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Western world.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.43,1:26:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pope said it's the Western civilization that's at risk.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.56,1:26:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Western civilization in 1955 calibrated over 205, 206.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.85,1:26:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrated 205.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.88,1:26:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1955, Western civilization calibrated at 205.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.42,1:26:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Can anybody hold that in their mind?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.71,1:26:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.22,1:27:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, currently, Western civilization calibrates over 199, 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.53,1:27:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.56,1:27:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It went down from 204, 205 to 199.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.26,1:27:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So, therefore, what the Pope said is true.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.59,1:27:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.59,1:27:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What the Pope said is true.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.19,1:27:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We are witnessing the decline of Western civilization, of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.81,1:27:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's already happened in Europe.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.81,1:27:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Europe's already had it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.81,1:27:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's already wimped out, I think it's called.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.53,1:27:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a new book that sounds startling.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:39.93,1:27:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It says something like,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.31,1:27:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Psycho's on the left of me, wimp's on the right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.14,1:27:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.32,1:28:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we see without personal responsibility at 475,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.32,1:28:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens is that free speech at 255
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.39,1:28:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,drops down to the level of narcissism.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.93,1:28:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of narcissism then,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.60,1:28:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,so narcissism and free speech then,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.60,1:28:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're doing is giving a loaded gun to children.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.73,1:28:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Free speech is a very powerful weapon.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.78,1:28:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And you put it in the hands of people who are not,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.92,1:28:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,don't take personal responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.92,1:28:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, out of free speech then becomes the tool of narcissism
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.14,1:28:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in which cultures that kill women for having been raped
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.34,1:28:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,are supposed to be welcomed into our society
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.59,1:28:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,where they can establish shiara.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.59,1:28:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Shiara calibrates at 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.57,1:29:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, honest dissent and disagree is 495.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.18,1:29:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The sophistry that goes with treason and sedition, et cetera,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.51,1:29:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is free speech.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.51,1:29:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,They say, well, that's just free speech.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.51,1:29:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.51,1:29:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Free speech is honest dissent.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.51,1:29:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I can disagree with many things in the government,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.51,1:29:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and I do.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.65,1:29:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't give you a nickel for most of it,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.65,1:29:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,but the way it runs, I mean,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.65,1:29:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,if you ran your own household that way,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.65,1:29:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd be bankrupt in no time.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.65,1:29:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.46,1:29:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,all right, so you don't have to go to sedition at 140
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.46,1:29:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,or treason at 105.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.88,1:29:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,During the break, we were remembering Tokyo Rose.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.88,1:29:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was the only one ever executed for treason
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.88,1:29:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in the last century, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.88,1:29:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Tokyo Rose during World War II.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.88,1:29:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there was Lord Ha Ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.03,1:30:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,These were anti-American treasonous and sedition.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.81,1:30:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So they could have, you could, so,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.81,1:30:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,your option is if you don't agree with the United States
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.81,1:30:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,or its politics or with the Republicans
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.84,1:30:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,or the Democrats or whoever,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.84,1:30:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you can be honest dissent and disagree,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.84,1:30:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's still integrous.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.89,1:30:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the option is to become a conscientious objector.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.10,1:30:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, conscientious objector calibrates over 300, 400, 375,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:40.11,1:30:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,375.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.11,1:30:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Conscientious objector is 375.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.11,1:30:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's integrous.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.25,1:30:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, I don't believe in killing people.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.25,1:30:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll serve in the military,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.63,1:30:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and I can do many things.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.63,1:30:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I can do warehousing.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.63,1:30:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I can do secretarial work, radio work.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.63,1:30:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I just, it's against my inner self.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.63,1:31:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I just can't kill another human being.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.63,1:31:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can be integrous,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.69,1:31:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and the option is not to become a deserter or a turncoat,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.69,1:31:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,but to be a conscientious objector.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.81,1:31:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't a conscientious objector,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.85,1:31:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm very happy that I never had to pull the trigger
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.52,1:31:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,on anybody in World War II.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.68,1:31:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, I never, I'm very happy I didn't have to be the gunner.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.68,1:31:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was the assistant bosun's mate at the time,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.89,1:31:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and all I had to do was keep the ship
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.00,1:31:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,from getting blown up by mines,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.00,1:31:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,but I didn't have to shoot anybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.22,1:31:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So that would be within myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.64,1:31:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I did not, you know, wish to be the agent
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.64,1:31:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,by which others are killed,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.64,1:31:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but I didn't make others wrong for doing it,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.64,1:31:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,because, you know, I could see how they saw their duty,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.64,1:31:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and I saw if I'd been ordered to do it,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.64,1:31:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose I would have,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.64,1:31:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,because I was respectful of authority,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.09,1:31:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and after all, you are in the war.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.63,1:32:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The U.S. National Anthem,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.63,1:32:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Pledge of Allegiance of the Flag,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.63,1:32:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 510.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.63,1:32:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Treason calibrates at 80.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.63,1:32:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So a Pledge of Allegiance then, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.85,1:32:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What it has, what it's really,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.85,1:32:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,your love of mankind,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.85,1:32:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,this is your love of country.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.85,1:32:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The National Anthem, et cetera,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.97,1:32:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it brings tears to many people's eyes.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.97,1:32:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You put your hand over what?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.97,1:32:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The National Anthem, you don't go like this,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.97,1:32:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that's military.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.97,1:32:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You put your hand over your heart,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.97,1:32:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's your love for your country,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.97,1:32:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,your esteem for your fellow man,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.97,1:32:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,your extended family,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.97,1:32:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,even if you disagree with them.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.97,1:32:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You can disagree with them.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.97,1:32:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't have to resort
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.97,1:32:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of, the opposite of patriotism
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.97,1:32:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and love of country and honor
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.97,1:32:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is not hate America.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.30,1:32:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So many now, and they're on television,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.42,1:32:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, television big names,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.48,1:33:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,specialize in hate America.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.97,1:33:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And the excuse is,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.22,1:33:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,because I disagree with its decisions.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.22,1:33:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not the only opposite.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.22,1:33:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You can honestly dissent and disagree
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.22,1:33:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and be 495,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.22,1:33:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don't have to be certain people
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.09,1:33:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,who instead hate.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:22.09,1:33:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, hate gets you good ratings, they say.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.09,1:33:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Playing the victim card, playing the race card,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.18,1:33:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the colored card, all this, you see?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.18,1:33:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hate America pays well.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.18,1:33:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Now Bush said one thing that we calibrated.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.14,1:33:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It was money trumps peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.48,1:33:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over 375, 380.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:50.28,1:33:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we calibrated 375.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.80,1:33:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Money trumps peace calibrates at 375.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.80,1:33:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.11,1:34:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Where does that put all the peace people?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.88,1:34:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They need more money.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:10.14,1:34:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They better start quick parades
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.14,1:34:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and start gathering money.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.77,1:34:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so I thought that's interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.01,1:34:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But I just want you to see honest dissent.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.06,1:34:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to become a traitor.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.06,1:34:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to go into sedition.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.06,1:34:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to vilify your country.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.06,1:34:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to vilify servicemen.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.06,1:34:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to vilify the president
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.06,1:34:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,or the United States of America.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.06,1:34:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You have an option to merely disagree.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:38.06,1:34:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Disagree.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.06,1:34:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.28,1:34:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that interesting?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.28,1:34:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody got any questions to clarify that?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.28,1:34:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's really important to see that,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.28,1:34:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that your option, you can still remain integrous
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.28,1:34:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and disagree.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.35,1:34:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,As I say, I disagree with a lot of things
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.35,1:34:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that go on with the government.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.35,1:34:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Both parties included, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.35,1:35:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't agree means I would do it differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.82,1:35:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But I just know that I would do it differently
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.98,1:35:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is only my personal opinion.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.98,1:35:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't feel that the world has to,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:12.25,1:35:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that I've made some pronouncement about reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:16.25,1:35:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Perception is reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.25,1:35:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.61,1:35:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's, any questions about that?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.61,1:35:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody, is it clear enough?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.61,1:35:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's clear, I'm very, very happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.61,1:35:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, boy, am I happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.61,1:35:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it might be difficult to get across.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.61,1:35:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we'll go to the next thing then.
